==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Springtail
<hw>Spring"tail`</hw> <pr>(-t⟦amac⟧l`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one of numerous species of small apterous
insects belonging to the order <ord>Thysanura</ord>. They have two
elastic caudal stylets which can be bent under the abdomen and then
suddenly extended like a spring, thus enabling them to leap to a
considerable distance. See <er>Collembola</er>, and
<er>Podura</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Springtide</ent>⟦br⟧
